1. *Pravda* je spora, ali dostižna. (Justice is slow, but achievable.)
2. Molim vas da mi pružite *pravdu*. (Please give me justice.)
3. Svi mi želimo *pravdu* za zločine počinjene u ratu. (We all want justice for war crimes.)
4. Sudija je odlučio u korist optuženog jer nije bilo dovoljno dokaza da se dokaže *pravda*. (The judge ruled in favor of the defendant because there wasn't enough evidence to prove justice.)
5. Ova država treba da uspostavi *pravni sistem* koji će osigurati jednakost pred zakonom. (This country needs to establish a legal system that will ensure equality before the law.)
6. Ona radi u *pravnoj kancelariji*. (She works at a law firm.)
7. Kada bi *pravda* bila dostižna za sve, svet bi bio bolje mesto. (If justice were achievable for everyone, the world would be a better place.)
8. *Pravdu* treba tražiti za sve žrtve nepravde. (Justice should be sought for all victims of injustice.)
9. Naša zemlja je poznata po *nepravdi* i korupciji. (Our country is known for injustice and corruption.)
10. Njihova organizacija se bori za *ljudska prava* i *pravdu*. (Their organization fights for human rights and justice.)